Elite Panzer IV Ausf. D X 2 @ 36<br />
Sturmpanzer IV &quot;Brummbär&quot; X1 @ 22   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">When setting up start out close to Flak. If there are no enemy planes don’t wait for the Flak, but start advancing. If the enemy is using planes start out with as many units in cover and as close to the Flak as possible. The Brummbär is the first one into cover. When advancing take out enemy armor first, and position the Brummbär to remove enemy infantry from the objective. BMW can support either one, but can also race toward an Anti tank gun or enemy commander. Against bigger tanks use the Panzers in pairs of a StuG and a Panzer IV. Rush forward with the StuG and hang back with the Panzer IV. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
